    <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
    <p>By listing your PG on our platform, you agree to the following terms and conditions:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><b> Accuracy of Information: </b>

            The owner/manager must provide accurate and up-to-date information about the PG.
            <br> FMPG reserves the right to verify and modify listings to ensure authenticity.
        </li>
        <li><b> Duration of Listing: </b>

            Listings will remain active for 7 days, after which they can be renewed or updated by the owner.
            <br> FMPG reserves the right to remove or suspend listings if they are found to be inaccurate or
            non-compliant.
        </li>
        <li><b> Fees and Payments: </b>
            FMPG may take a commission from successful bookings, as per prior agreement.
        </li>
        <li><b> Termination: </b>

            FMPG can terminate listings that violate local laws, fail to meet quality standards, or receive
            repeated complaints.
            <br> The owner may remove their listing at any time, provided there are no pending bookings.
        </li>
        <li><b> Dispute Resolution: </b>

            FMPG will act as an intermediary in case of disputes between tenants and owners but will not be held
            liable for legal matters.
            <br> Both parties agree to settle disputes through arbitration or mediation, as outlined by FMPG’s
            policies.
        </li>
        <li><b> Liability: </b>

            FMPG will not be responsible for any false representation by the owner or the tenant.
            <br> Owners are responsible for ensuring the safety and legality of their PG property.
            <br> This should cover the basics, ensuring clarity for both the property owners and potential
            tenants. You can customize or add more conditions depending on your business policies.


        </li>

        <h1> Additional Requirements for Listing a PG: </h1>

        <li><b> Tenant Preferences: </b>

            Gender preference (if specific): Male/Female/Co-ed.
            <br>Age group (e.g., students, working professionals).
            <br>Smoking/alcohol consumption policy.
        </li>
        <li><b> Security Measures: </b>

            Availability of CCTV cameras, security guards, or gated entry.
            <br> Lockable individual rooms or lockers for personal belongings.
        </li>
        <li><b> Maintenance and Services: </b>

            Details of any regular maintenance services provided (plumbing, electrical, etc.).
            <br> Frequency of room cleaning and trash collection.
        </li>
        <li><b> Occupancy Details: </b>

            Total number of tenants currently staying in the PG.
            <br> Maximum allowed occupancy per room and for the entire PG.
            <br> Terms for sharing common areas like bathrooms and kitchen.
        </li>
        <li><b> Payment Methods:</b>

            Accepted payment methods (cash, bank transfer, UPI, digital wallets, etc.).
            <br> Clarity on payment timelines (e.g., rent due date, advance payment policy).
            <br> Policy on late payments, penalties, and refund conditions.
        </li>
        <li><b> Special Offers: </b>

            Details of any seasonal discounts, referral bonuses, or early-bird offers.
            <br> Options for rent bundling with services ( meals, laundry, etc.).
        </li>

        <li><b> Verification of Tenants: </b>

            Owners are responsible for tenant verification, ensuring that the tenant provides government ID and adheres to local tenant laws.
            <br> FMPG may assist with third-party verification services (if offered).
        </li>
        <li><b> Tenant Contract: </b>

            Owners are encouraged to provide a rental agreement or contract, outlining the terms of stay, rent, security deposit, and any other rules.
           <br> The rental agreement should comply with local real estate and rental laws.
        </li>
        <li><b> Review and Feedback Mechanism: </b>

            Owners must allow tenants to leave honest reviews about the property and their experience.
            <br> Owners can reply to tenant feedback to clarify or address issues raised.
        </li>
        <li><b> Insurance and Safety: </b>

            It is advised that owners have appropriate insurance for the property (e.g., fire or theft
            insurance).
            <br> FMPG is not liable for any property damage or loss incurred on the premises.
        </li>
        <li><b> Code of Conduct: </b>

            PG owners must maintain a standard of conduct, treating all tenants with respect and fairness.

        </li>
        <li><b> Regular Updates: </b>

            Owners are required to regularly update the status of room availability, pricing, and amenities.
            <br> FMPG may periodically request updates to ensure the listing remains accurate and competitive.
        </li>
        <li><b> Marketing and Promotion: </b>

            By listing on FMPG, the owner agrees that their property details may be used in FMPG's marketing campaigns (emails, social media, etc.) to attract potential tenants.
            <br> FMPG will not share personal contact details publicly without the owner’s consent.
        </li>
        <li><b> Exclusive Listing Option (Optional): </b>

            Owners can opt for exclusive listings, where their PG is promoted as a premium property on FMPG for a
            certain fee.
           <br> Exclusive listings may receive special marketing attention, priority in search results, or featured
            placements.
        </li>
        <li><b> Support and Dispute Escalation: </b>

            FMPG provides 24/7 customer support for handling issues related to the listing or bookings.
            <br> Disputes between owners and tenants must first be escalated to FMPG before pursuing legal
            action.

        <li><b> Data Privacy: </b>

            All personal information provided by the owner and tenants will be protected as per FMPG's privacy
            policy.
            <br> FMPG will not sell or misuse owner/tenant data for any unauthorized purposes.
        </li>
